==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[croc]]'', "hook".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-crotch.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''crotch'''
# The [[area]] where something [[fork|forks]] or [[branches]], a [[ramification]] takes place.
#:''There is a [[child]] sitting in a crotch of that [[tree]].''
# (''slang'') The ([[ventral]]) area of a person's body where the [[leg|legs]] fork from the [[trunk]].
#:''He was kicked in his crotch.''
====Translations====
*French: [[fourche]] ''f'' (1)
*German: [[Gabelung]] ''f'' (1), [[Schritt]] ''m'' (2)
*Swedish: (gren)[[klyka]] {{c}} (1), [[skrev]] {{n}} (2), [[gren]] {{c}} (2)

